---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";

// Personal Data Protection / Privacy Policy.
// NOTE: [BRACKETED] items must be completed with the registered company details
// before this is treated as final. Review by a qualified lawyer is recommended.
const updated = "21 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  current="home"
  title="Privacy & Data Protection — Coworking Prilep"
  description="How Coworking Prilep collects, uses, and protects the personal data of website visitors and card users, in line with the Law on Personal Data Protection of North Macedonia."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="How we protect the personal data of website visitors and card users. Aligned with the Law on Personal Data Protection of the Republic of North Macedonia (Official Gazette 42/2020) and the GDPR."
  />

  <article class="px-6 pb-24 md:px-12 md:pb-32">
    <div class="prose-cws mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.25em] text-bone/40 uppercase">
        Last updated: {updated}
      </p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        This website (coworkingprilep.mk) is operated by
        <strong>Dastian DOO Prilep</strong> (the "Company", "we", "us"), which runs
        Coworking Prilep through its branch <strong>BLOK 02</strong> in Prilep,
        North Macedonia. For the purposes of data protection law, we are the
        <strong>data controller</strong> of the personal data described below.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Registered name:</strong> Друштво за производство, промет, услуги и трговија ДАСТИАН увоз-извоз ДОО Прилеп (Dastian DOO Prilep)</li>
        <li><strong>Registered seat:</strong> Kej 1-vi Maj no. 9, Prilep, North Macedonia</li>
        <li><strong>Coworking location (branch BLOK 02):</strong> Jane Sandanski no. 33, Prilep</li>
        <li><strong>Company reg. no. (ЕМБС):</strong> 7821808</li>
        <li><strong>Tax no. (ЕДБ):</strong> 4021025551046</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:coworkingprilep@outlook.com">coworkingprilep@outlook.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what we need to run the service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact data</strong> — your email address when you join our
          pre-launch list, and your name and email if you contact us or create a
          booking or membership.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Payment data</strong> — when you pay by card, the payment is
          processed directly by ProCredit Bank's secure payment gateway. We
          <strong>do not receive, see, or store your full card number, expiry, or
          CVV</strong>. We may retain a transaction reference, the last four
          digits of the card, the amount, and the date for accounting and
          support.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage &amp; device data</strong> — with your consent, we use
          analytics tools that collect information such as pages viewed, approximate
          location, device and browser type, and interactions with the site.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical logs</strong> — our servers record standard data such
          as IP address and request time for security and reliability.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Why we use it and our legal basis</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>To provide the service</strong> (accounts, bookings, memberships) — performance of a contract.</li>
        <li><strong>To process payments and issue receipts/invoices</strong> — contract and legal obligation.</li>
        <li><strong>To send you updates you asked for</strong> (pre-launch and service emails) — your consent.</li>
        <li><strong>To keep the site secure and improve it</strong> (analytics) — your consent and our legitimate interest.</li>
        <li><strong>To meet accounting and tax duties</strong> — legal obligation.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Cookies &amp; analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We show a cookie banner on your first visit. Analytics and any
        non-essential cookies load <strong>only after you accept</strong>. We use
        Google Analytics (aggregate visitor statistics) and Microsoft Clarity
        (anonymous session insights and heatmaps). You can change or withdraw your
        choice at any time by clearing the site's cookies and reloading.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Who we share data with</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal data. We share it only with service providers
        that help us operate, each bound to protect it and use it only on our
        instructions:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>ProCredit Bank / its card processor</strong> — to process card payments.</li>
        <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — database and authentication hosting.</li>
        <li><strong>Resend</strong> — sending transactional and confirmation emails.</li>
        <li><strong>Google (Analytics)</strong> and <strong>Microsoft (Clarity)</strong> — website analytics, subject to your consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Our hosting provider</strong> — running the website infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We may also disclose data where required by law or to protect our legal
        rights.
      </p>

      <h2>6. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some of our providers process data outside North Macedonia, including in
        the EU and the USA. Where this happens, we rely on appropriate safeguards
        (such as providers' standard contractual clauses and adequacy measures) to
        protect your data to the standard required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>7. How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal data only as long as necessary: subscriber and marketing
        data until you unsubscribe or ask us to delete it; account, booking, and
        membership data for the life of your relationship with us; and
        payment/invoice records for the period required by tax and accounting law
        (currently up to 10 years).
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under the Law on Personal Data Protection you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>access the data we hold about you;</li>
        <li>correct inaccurate data;</li>
        <li>delete your data ("right to be forgotten");</li>
        <li>restrict or object to certain processing;</li>
        <li>receive your data in a portable format;</li>
        <li>withdraw consent at any time (without affecting past processing).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these, email
        <a href="mailto:coworkingprilep@outlook.com">coworkingprilep@outlook.com</a>.
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the
        <strong>Agency for Personal Data Protection of North Macedonia</strong>
        (Агенција за заштита на личните податоци, <a href="https://azlp.mk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">azlp.mk</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>9. How we protect your data</h2>
      <p>
        The site is served over encrypted HTTPS (TLS). Access to our database is
        restricted with row-level security and role-based controls, and card data
        is handled entirely within the bank's PCI-DSS-compliant gateway. We apply
        appropriate technical and organisational measures to guard against
        unauthorised access, loss, or misuse.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Our services are intended for people aged 18 and over. We do not knowingly
        collect data from children.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date at the
        top shows the current version. Material changes will be highlighted on this
        page.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy or your data? Email
        <a href="mailto:coworkingprilep@outlook.com">coworkingprilep@outlook.com</a>
        or write to Dastian DOO Prilep, Kej 1-vi Maj no. 9, Prilep, North Macedonia.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
